description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, friendly , energetic, motivated with a &#39;can do&#39; attitude part-time housekeeping supervisor willing to work hard within a strong team. They will be required to provide a KEY service within theorganisation for both staff and patients. The successful candidate will assist with all associated duties connected with the delivery of housekeeping services. They will deal with cleaning services in patients’ wards, clinical and non-clinical areas. The post-holder will be required to adhere to departmental standards and regulations. They will also act at all times in a manner that upholds the Trust’s values, working as part of a team to ensure efficiency and excellent customer care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging but rewarding job and would be ideally suited to a motivated team player. Supervisory experience is desirable along with a good level of English and maths. Knowledge of COSHH, BICSc, and infection control is also desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours to be covered are 26.5 hours per week working 5 days out of 7 on a rota system. This will include alternate weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
